<HEADLINE> Russian-Iranian Memorandum on Nuclear Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Yevgeny
Primakov and Iranian Parliament Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri
today signed a memorandum of mutual understanding on export
controls.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Foreign Ministry said the memorandum reaffirms
commitment of the two states to non-proliferation of nuclear
weapons, and of their carriers.
</P>
<P>
The commitment indicates cooperation bilaterally and
multilaterally to prevent the use for undeclared purposes of
technical means and technologies subject to export controls.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation would be carried out within the framework of
corresponding international obligations and treaties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
