<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at GMT 1600, April 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME -- Italy's 11-months-old government won a vote of
confidence in parliament's lower house Saturday, clearing a
challenge from the right-wing opposition seeking to block a
security force for stricken Albania.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- The Shroud of Turin, revered by many Roman Catholics as
the burial cloth of Jesus Christ, narrowly escaped incineration
Saturday when a fire gutted the chapel where it is housed.
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Union (EU) and the United States have
reached a deal on their trade dispute over Washington's anti-Cuba
law, the Helms-Burton Act. The deal would allow the EU to suspend
a panel it had established at the World Trade Organization in
Geneva.
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi told the Chamber of
Deputies(lower house) Saturday that the bulk of Italian troops
will leave for Albania next Tuesday to participate the Italy-led
Operation Sunrise to aid Albania.
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT - Lebanese Foreign Minister Farez Boueiz announced here
Saturday that he will urge the European and Mediterranean
countries at a Malta gathering to freeze their relations with
Israel.
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's Congress Party said Saturday that the
party's claim for power was over and that it would support the
United Front (UF) in forming a new government if the UF changes
its leader.
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan expects that the
U.N. Security Council Sanctions Committee will renew the
oil-for-food deal with Iraq for another six-month term, an Iraqi
newspaper reported Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
