<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Awards Russian Cosmonauts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
signed a decree today granting state awards to outstanding
cosmonauts on the Day of Cosmonautics.
</P>
<P>
Spaceship commander Valery Korzun was granted the title of Hero
of the Russian Federation for his long space mission of the 22d
main expedition aboard the Mir complex, According to the Itar-Tass
news agency,
</P>
<P>
Flight engineer Alexander Kaleri was awarded the order For
Services for the Fatherland and Korzun also received the title of
Pilot-Cosmonaut of the Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, for a great contribution to the development of
domestic aviation and cosmonautics, head of the flight test center
and deputy head of the Gromov research institute Igor Volk was
awarded the order For Services for the Fatherland.
</P>
<P>
April 12 was set as the Cosmonautics Day of Russia to mark Yuri
Gagarin's first ever space flight on board of the Vostok
spacecraft in 1961. 
</P>
</TEXT>
