<HEADLINE> Cost Sharing in Education Urged in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Forty-four percent of the fund
allocated to the Zambian Education Ministry is being channeled to
the two local universities and there is urgent need to introduce
cost sharing, a educational official said today.
</P>
<P>
Permanent secretary of the ministry, Sichalwe Kasanda, told
the Zambia News Agency in Livingstone, southern Zambia, that
parents should contribute to higher education.
</P>
<P>
Kasanda said students who demanded a loan will require
involvement of immigration, customs and legal backing to monitor
recovery.
</P>
<P>
"We have a culture of making rules but not implementing them.
That is why we are restructuring public service to build
capacity," he complained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
