<HEADLINE> PNA Demands Israel Halt Judaization of Jerusalem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian National
Authority (PNA) today warned of grave consequences if Israel does
not change its policy of Judaization in Jerusalem, the state-run
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The PNA, which issued the warning in a statement at the end of
its weekly cabinet session in Gaza, also demanded that the
hardline Netanyahu government stop settlement expansion in the
West Bank and Gaza Strip.
</P>
<P>
However, the PNA stated that it is committed to the peace
process despite current problems with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The PNA also paid tribute to Palestinian protesters who
had clashed with Israeli troops almost on the daily basis for
the past three weeks in various autonomous cities.
</P>
<P>
In another development, according to a report from Washington,
PLO Secretary General Abu Mazen, accompanied by PNA ministers Saeb
Erekat and Hanan Ashrawi, held talks with U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright and Middle East peace coordinator Dennis Ross
on how to get the derailed peace process back on track.
</P>
<P>
But there is no sign indicating that Albright is planning a
visit to the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian negotiators demanded that Israel give back to
Palestinians more territories in the first phase of the withdrawal
from the West Bank following the Hebron agreement, which was
signed in January.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, fresh street battle between rock-throwing
Palestinian youths and well-armed Israeli army soldiers broke out
again in Hebron today. Hundreds of Palestinian youths confronted
the soldiers with a barrage of rocks.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers responded with rubber bullets and tear gas,
injuring five stone-throwers.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian police intervened, but failed to control the
demonstrators. Several youths took up positions on rooftops and
dropped rocks on the Israeli soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The Hebron violence has already continued for five consecutive
days. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
