<HEADLINE> UK Demonstrators Attack Major's Residence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A protest march through London
turned violent today, with thousands of demonstrators scuffling
with policemen and attacking Prime Minister John Major's residence
in Downing Street, BBC television reported today.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that an orange smoke bomb was thrown into the
entrance of Downing Street and distress flares let off.
</P>
<P>
Some of the 3,500-strong crowd taking part in the event pelted
police in riot gear with white paint and beer.
</P>
<P>
The "social justice" march, which was aimed at highlighting
attacks on living standards, was also joined in by the "direct
action" environmental activists, who oppose new road-building
schemes and the use of cars, and groups of unemployed, disabled
and asylum seekers were also among those demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
The marchers later rallied in Trafalgar Square where there was
singing and speeches were delivered. 
</P>
</TEXT>
