<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congolese President in Kinshasa on Zaire Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZZAVILLE, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Congolese President Pascal
Lissouba went to Kinshasa this afternoon to meet Zairian President
Mobutu Sese Seko on the Zaire crisis, said officials of the
Congolese presidential office.
</P>
<P>
Officials said that Lissouba will try to persuade President
Mobutu to meet the chief of the Zairian rebellion, Laurentg-Desire
Kabila, in the Congolese city of Pointe Noire, as was suggested by
Lissouba earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The summit of the Customs and Economic Union of central African
countries held this week in Brazzaville encouraged Lissouba, who
is president of the Consultative Committee on African Security of
the United Nations, to mediate between Mobutu and Kabila.
</P>
<P>
Zairian Foreign Minister Gerard Kamanda wa Kamanda will also
visit Brazzaville Sunday to meet Congolese officials on the crisis
in his country.
</P>
<P>
Kabila has given Mobutu three days to meet him on condition of
his resignation from the presidency of Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu has rejected the ultimatum, but said he does not oppose
meeting Kabila. 
</P>
