<HEADLINE> Morocco Calls French Process of Visa Application </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Moroccan Interior Minister Driss
Hasri today described France's long processing of visa application
by Moroccans as "unacceptable," and said that he had raised the
issue with President Jacques Chirac.
</P>
<P>
The Agence France-Presse quoted Hasri as saying today in Paris
that France's crackdown on illegal immigrants has "touched the
base" of regular immigration and normal circulation of people to
France.
</P>
<P>
"This is a question of principle and national dignity. We will
not accept such red tape," Hasri said, adding that "France would
be the loser" if it did not change its policy of visa processing.
</P>
<P>
He said that Moroccan businessmen can go to Germany, the United
States and Britain without having to wait for two months for their
visas as they do for going to France.
</P>
<P>
France and Morocco will set up a joint committee to study the
problem, he said. 
</P>
