<HEADLINE> Nigeria Questions Switzerland for Maltreatment of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian mission in Geneva has
demanded an explanation from the Swiss government of the
maltreatment of Clement Nwankwo, a Nigerian citizen.
</P>
<P>
The News Agency of Nigeria said in a report today that
Nigeria's permanent representative to the United Nations in
Geneva, Ejoh Abuah, has delivered a strongly-worded letter to the
Swiss government on the matter.
</P>
<P>
