53rd session of the U.N. Commission on Human Rights in Geneva,
the report said.
</P>
<P>
It continued that Nwankwo was accused of shoplifting and
suffered "four days of humiliation, degradation, torture and
punishment" before his conviction.
</P>
<P>
Nwankwo himself claimed that during his arrest, he was hit in
the face by one of the policemen and his glasses were smashed
while one of the policemen "put his baton on my neck and squeezed
real hard."
</P>
<P>
He was swiftly deported after his conviction by the court, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian mission lamented that Nwankwo was deported even
while the appeal for his conviction was still pending and without
contacting it, a move which they said was contrary to diplomatic
practice.
</P>
<P>
Delegates attending the session of the Human Rights Commission
have expressed their shock at the occurrence of such an event in
a city housing the U.N. human rights center, the report said.
</P>
<P>
They were also quoted as saying that similar cases had
happened in the past, especially against colored people. 
</P>
