<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Foreign Currency Black Market to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A senior Ethiopian
government official said today that the black market to exchange
U.S. Dollar would soon "die its natural death."
</P>
<P>
Fantaye Biftu, head of the Trade and Finance Supervision
Bureau in the Prime Minsiter's Office, said the illegal exchange
market was of no benefit as the margin between the prices at
banks and the black market has already narrowed.
</P>
