awareness of investment opportunities in Nepal, it added.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Jayakumar and concerned Nepali officials held
discussions over Nepal's proposal to seek help from Singapore for
promoting high quality tourism, the communique said.
</P>
<P>
Tourism promotion boards of the two countries will meet soon to
share experiences and explore a plan of action at the earliest, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The communique also said that the Singapore foreign minister
responded positively to Nepal's desire to seek cooperation for the
establishment of an information technology park in Nepal.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure for Dhaka, Bangladesh today, Jayakumar
told reporters at the airport that the objective of his visit was
to promote bilateral cooperation in economic development, tourism
and technology sectors.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need of discussions between business
communities of both countries for identifying the opportunities of
foreign investment in Nepal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
