<HEADLINE> Chinese Take Three Singles Titles at Asian Junior </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- China took three of five singles
competitions while Indonesia and Malaysia claimed one each in the
final round of the seven-day Asian Junior Badminton Championships
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's Taufik Hidayat, 16-year-old third seed, won the
boys' title by beating China's Chen Hong, 15-11, 15-2.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very happy," said Hidayat, who entered the finals with a
stunning victory over top seed Xia Xuanze of China in Saturday's
semifinal.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Gong Ruina grabbed the girls' singles title after
winning over compatriot Zhou Mi, 11-5, 11-5.
</P>
<P>
In the mixed doubles competition, top seed Cheng Rui and Gao
Ling of China played with awesome teamwork to beat Malaysians Chan
Chong Ming and Lim Pek Siah, 15-7, 15-9 in 45 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the girls' doubles, China's Gao Ling and Yang Wei dominated
Malaysians Chor Hooi Yee and Lim Pek Siah, winning by 15-10, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
But Chinese suffered a heavy defeat at the hands of Malaysia in
the boys' doubles. Malaysians Chan Chong Ming and Jeremy Gan beat
top favorite Zhang Yi and Cai Yun of China, 15-6, 15-3, to take
the crown.
</P>
<P>
China also won the men's and women's team titles on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The championships, which opened Monday, included teams from
Singapore, Iran, Macau, India, the Philippines, Vietnam, Pakistan,
Cambodia, Nepal, Burma, Bangladesh, Kazakstan and Syria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
