<HEADLINE> Strong Aftershock Hits Southwest Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An aftershock measuring 5.5 on
the Richter Scale hit Jiashi County in the southwestern part of
the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region today, according to the State
Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
No one was reported dead in the aftershock though it occurred
in the early morning.
</P>
<P>
It is one of 364 aftershocks of an earthquake that occurred in
Jiashi County on April 11, which measured 6.6 on the Richter
Scale. The earthquake claimed the lives of nine people, and injured
49, 30 of them seriously.
</P>
<P>
The quake, the latest in a series of recent quakes in Jiashi
County, damaged more than 73,000 rooms and 15 mosques, and killed
more than 1,500 head of livestock.  
</P>
