<HEADLINE> Beijing is getting rid of dustbins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Clean and elegant garbage houses
will replace the dirty and rusty iron dustbins that are scattered
on street corners or near public toilets later this year.
</P>
<P>
By the year's end, Beijing will have 761 garbage collecting
depots, according to the city's environmental sanitation
department.
</P>
<P>
Sanitation workers will go to each household to collect garbage
bags and take them to the garbage houses.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 600,000 households and 10,000 office buildings
have started collecting their refuse in garbage bags. 
