<HEADLINE> Thai Saman Retains WBC Light Flyweight Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Saman Sor-Chaturong
defended his World Boxing Council (WBC) light flyweight title
Sunday with a seventh round technical knockout against number six
contender Julio Coronel of Colombia in Chaiyaphum, Thailand.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Saman dominated the bout with powerful right
and left hooks to the head and body of his one-year-junior rival.
</P>
<P>
Although Coronel offered resistance with left jabs and straight
rights to the face, the Thai took control the fight from the fifth
round onwards.
</P>
<P>
Early in the seventh, Saman landed a very fast and powerful
right hook to the chin, sending Coronel down for his second
eight-count during the match, before the referee stopped the fight
with 40 seconds of the round gone.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, Saman improved his fight record to 34 wins
(30 knockouts), one draw and two losses, while Coronel's record
now stands at 23 wins (18 knockouts), two draws, and five
defeats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
