<HEADLINE> Shooting Occurs at Israeli-Jordanian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli security guards
were shot and lightly wounded today at the Allenby Bridge
(Hussein Bridge) between Israel and Jordan, Israel Radio
reported.
</P>
<P>
A woman, apparently having gone through Jordanian security
checks, crossed the bridge, and suddenly opened fire as she
approached the security guards, said the report. But the radio
neither identified the attacker nor gave other details on the
shooting.
</P>
<P>
Earlier last month, seven Israeli schoolgirls were killed
and six others wounded, when a crazy Jordanian soldier shot them
to death as they toured the Jordanian-controlled Naharayim
enclave at the Jordan Valley.
</P>
<P>
Later King Hussein of Jordan paid a condolence visit to
Israel, going house to house to visit the bereaved families of
the seven victims, pledging to push forward the peace process.
