<HEADLINE> Top legislator Stresses Efforts against separatism in Xinjiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 13 (XINHUA) -- China must take a resolute stand
against national separatism by religious extremists in the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, Chinese top legislator Qiao Shi
stated here today.
</P>
<P>
"We must firmly oppose national separatism and religious
extremist forces, and safeguard the dignity of laws and the
fundamental interests of people of various ethnic groups," Qiao
Shi, chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's
Congress (NPC), said in a meeting with the region's senior Party,
government and military leaders this morning.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, made a
stopover in Urumqi on his way to Mongolia after visiting several
European countries.
</P>
<P>
"Opposing religious extremist forces has been the common action
taken by the majority of the countries in the world, including
some Western countries," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"We must always guard against and strike hard at activities to
split the unification of the motherland and undermine unity among
people of various ethnic groups," he said, "it will be our
top priority work at present and a task for a long time to come."
</P>
<P>
"As a region inhabited by 47 different ethnic groups, Xinjiang
must take effective measures to strengthen the unity among people
of various ethnic groups," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"We must always bear in mind the idea that 'Han people can not
live without the ethnic minorities and the ethnic minorities
cannot live without the Han people'," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Priority should be given to the legitimate special interests
of ethnic minority people, so that people of ethnic groups will
improve their living standards substantially, and make new
achievements in their social undertakings and cultural progress,"
he told local officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0062 </DOCNO>
