<HEADLINE> Ramos Appoints Acting Transportation Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today announced the appointment of former Armed Forces Chief of
Staff Auturo Enrile as Acting Secretary of the Department of
Transportation and Communications effective on April 16.
</P>
<P>
Enrile, 56, will replace Transportation and Communications
Secretary Amado Lagdameo, who resigned on March 24 for his alleged
involvement in the Manila Bay "land scam".
</P>
<P>
A native of Lucena City, Enrile finished his Bachelor of
Science at the Philippine Military Academy in 1962, after studying
for two years at the College of Engineering of the University of
the Philippines in Quezon City.
</P>
<P>
Enrile was twice conferred the Philippine Legion of Honor by
President Ramos for his outstanding performance as Commanding
General of the Philippine Army and as Chief of Staff of the Armed
Forces.
</P>
<P>
He was also a recipient of numerous medals for combat, staff
and managerial achievements.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also appointed former Head Executive Assistant in the
Office of the Secretary of the Department of Transportation and
Communications Arturo Valdez as Undersecretary of the Department.
</P>
</TEXT>
