<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Northeast Province Intensifies Forest Fireproofing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Forest fire prevention has been
given closer attention in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province,
which has not seen any forest fire during the past three years in
its 175 counties.
</P>
<P>
Heilongjiang Province is rich in forest resources. Ten years
ago, a big forest fire hitted the province on May 6. The whole
nation was shocked by the huge damage caused by the fire.
</P>
<P>
Since then, the province has stepped up its forest fire
prevention efforts by building up fire lanes, increasing the funds
for fireproofing, and improving facilities.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that during the past three years the province
has spent 95.38 million yuan (12 million US dollars) on forest
fire prevention, and monitor more than 90 percent of the forest
areas.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 8,536 Professional forest fire fighters
and 140,000 voluntary fire fighters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
