<HEADLINE> HKSAR Independent Commission Seeks Public's Advice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The Independent Commission on
Remuneration for Members of the Executive Council and the
Legislature of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
 today called on citizens to air their views on the issues which
the commission is examining.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the commission said here today that while the
commission shall make reference to the existing system, it would
welcome comments from members of the public on a whole range of
issues it should consider.
</P>
<P>
He said the views from the citizens will help the commission
work out reasonable, equitable and feasible recommendations.
</P>
<P>
He said comments from the public can be sent in writing or by
fax by April 26 to the secretary of the commission.
</P>
<P>
Appointed by HKSAR Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa in March, the
commission is in charge of recommending to Tung the appropriate
levels of remuneration for members of the Executive Council and
the Provisional Legislative Council before July 1.
</P>
<P>
The commission should also look at whether any changes should
be made to the remuneration packages after July 1. In addition,
the terms of reference of the commission cover matters pertaining
to the remuneration of the members of the First Legislative
Council and the arrangements for those with multiple memberships
on the above bodies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
