<HEADLINE> Velez Sarsfield Beats River Plate in Recopa Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Velez Sarsfield edged River Plate
4-2 on penalty in an all-Argentine clash Sunday at the South
American Recopa Final in Kobe, Japan, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The annual match was played between the South American Super
Cup and Libertadores Cup soccer champions.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, the two sides played to a
1-1 tie in the regulation 90 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In a action-packed contest before 20,000 Japanese fans at Kobe
Universidade Stadium, Super Cup champion Velez Sarsfield's
goalkeeper Jose Luis Chilavert converted a penalty kick in the
29th minute to open the scorings.
</P>
<P>
Uruguayan forward Enzo Francescoli of Libertadores Cup champion
River Plate pulled back, also through a penalty kick, in the 82nd
minute.
</P>
<P>
Japan has been the venue for the past few years for a one-game
final instead of home-and-away formula to determine the year's
best South American team.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian team Gremio beat Independiente of Argentina 4-1 in
last year's Recopa Final. 
</P>
</TEXT>
