<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Export Earnings Up During First Eight Months in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's export earnings has
gone up by nearly 14 billion taka (about 350 million US dollars)
during the first eight months of the current fiscal compared to
that of the same period of last financial year, said the Export
Promotion Bureau (EPB).
</P>
<P>
During the period from July, 1996 to February, 1997,
Bangladesh's total earning from the export of both primary and
manufactured items rose by 13.12 percent to 120.66 billion taka
(about 3.01 billion US dollars), said an EPB report released here
today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that of the total earnings, the traditional raw
jute and jute goods contributed 12.05 billion taka (about 301
million US dollars) or 9.99 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the export earnings from manufactured commodities
reached 105.12 billion taka (about 2.63 billion US dollars), which
is 87.13 percent of the total earnings.
</P>
<P>
Among the major items, export receipts from ready-made garments
during the period rose by 8.38 percent to 59.86 billion taka
(about 1.49 billion US dollars) while the export from knitwear
went up by 33.41 percent to 21.02 billion taka (about 525 million
US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Frozen food including shrimps and fish, leather and leather
goods and tea are also contributing heavily to the increase of the
export earnings during the first eight months of this fiscal year,
the report added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italians Take Two Titles at Malaysian Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Italians Valentino Rossi and
Max Biaggi won the 125 c.c and the 250 c.c. respectively while
Michaell Doohan of Australia took the 500 c.c. class at the
Malaysian Grand Prix for Motorcycles on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rossi on an Aprilia beat Kazuto Sakata of Japan in the last lap
to win the 125 c.c. 29 lap race covering 101.645 kilometers with a
time of 48 minutes 09.93 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Sakata, also on an Aprilia, clocked 48:10.924, while a distant
third was Japanese Noboru Ueda on a Honda with 48:42.128.
</P>
<P>
Three time world champion Biaggi made it a day for the Italians
when he powered his Honda to a comfortable victory in the 250
c.c. event, timing 45:29.692 over 31 laps.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Tetsuya Harada, who switched to Aprilia this year from
Yamaha, was a distant second in 45:43.562.
</P>
<P>
Doohan, also a three time world champion, confirmed his
supremacy in the 500 c.c. 33 lap race, amounting to about 116
kilometers by winning the Prix here, timing 47 minutes 11.545
seconds.
</P>
<P>
His teammate Alex Criville from Spain was a distant second at
47:23.341, closely followed by newcomer Nobuatsu Aoki of Japan in
third place, clocking 47:24.948. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
