<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Service Industry Contributes Half of Revenues in Shenyang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- The service sector in Shenyang,
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province, contributed 40
percent to the local total revenues in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Efforts to restructure the city's industrial setup to develop
the service industry began in 1990. Great changes have taken place
in the previous economic structure in which industry outweighed
agriculture and services in Shenyang, one of the country's
traditional industrial bases.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, the annual growth rate of revenues from local
industry has reached 10.89 percent, compared to 19.68 percent from
the local service trade.
</P>
<P>
The service industry now accounts for the bulk of local
revenues, having gained nine percent more compared to 1991.
</P>
<P>
The distribution business has witnessed the fastest development
among the local service industries, bringing in a total of nearly
5.3 billion yuan in revenues to the city during the 1991-1995
period.
</P>
<P>
Other service industries such as finance, insurance,
service, transportation, and posts and telecommunications,
all have shown a tendency toward rapid growth. enditem
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
