<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Leader Arrives in Ulan Bator for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC),
arrived here today for a three-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
Qiao came from Urumqi, the capital of China's Xinjiang
Autonomous Region, where he made a stopover following his six-day
visit to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia is the last leg of his Europe and Asia tour, which has
already taken him to France, Norway and Italy. This is the first
visit to Mongolia by a Chinese NPC leader.
</P>
<P>
Qiao is here at the invitation of Chairman Radnaasumberel
Gonchigdorj of Mongolia's Great Hural.
</P>
<P>
He was greeted at the airport by senior officials from the
Great Hural and Chinese Ambassador to Mongolia Qi Zhijia.
</P>
<P>
In a statement at the airport, Qiao said that he hoped his
visit will help enhance the mutual understanding and friendship
between China and Mongolia and strengthen the good relations
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and Mongolia are neighbors linked by
mountains and rivers and the Chinese and Mongolian people have
been friendly to each other for years.
</P>
<P>
Since the normalization of diplomatic relations between the two
countries, Qiao said, China and Mongolia have continued to develop
their friendly ties and cooperation and the Chinese NPC has
maintained good relations and exchanges with the Great Hural.
</P>
<P>
He said that good-neighborly relations between the two
countries not only benefit the two peoples but are also conducive
to peace and development in the region.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Qiao is scheduled to hold talks with
Mongolian President Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat, Great Hural Chairman
Gonchigdorj, Prime Minister Mendsaikhan Enkhsaikhan on bilateral
relations and issues of common interest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
