<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Issues Property Right Certificates To Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 20,000 state-owned
enterprises in China's largest industrial city of Shanghai will
have been granted state property right certificates by mid-year.
</P>
<P>
Any enterprise which doesn't have the certificate by then will
not be entitled to operate, according to the Municipal Office of
State Property Administration.
</P>
<P>
The program, started Wednesday, is aimed at explicitly defining
state property and speeding up the establishment of a modern
enterprise system and other supporting mechanisms.
</P>
<P>
The office will register the property, liability-asset, rights
and interests of the owners of the enterprises, and confirm the
property's legal status by issuing the certificates.
</P>
<P>
The registration system can also record occurrences, changes
and cancellation of state property, and help to exercise
supervision over and management of the state property operation,
in order to preserve and increase its value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
