<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 08:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netanyahu, Peres Meet Secretly on Forming Unity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu and opposition leader Shimon Peres have
discussed secretly the idea of forming a national unity
government, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
The two held a secret meeting at Netanyahu's residence in
Jerusalem last week before Netanyahu departed for his European
tour, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in Italy over the weekend, Netanyahu
said he was considering forming a unity government with the
Labor Party in order to advance the final-status talks with the
Palestinian National Authority (PNA). But he added he had yet
made a formal decision.
</P>
<P>
Peres, currently visiting Brazil, will return home this week
to convene a Central Committee meeting of the Labor Party, in a
bid to muster support on forming a national unity government
with Netanyahu's Likud Party.
</P>
<P>
Aiming to rescue the peace process that he champions, Peres
has been an enthusiastic advocate of the unity government.
</P>
<P>
The Labor leader is eager to join such a government before a
new party leader is elected in the June 3 primary. He will thus
become the senior Labor minister and retain the leadership
status no matter who is elected in his stead.
</P>
<P>
For this reason, Ehud Barak, Peres' possible successor,
strongly opposes the idea of a unity government. He vowed that
he would topple the Netanyahu government rather than rescuing it
by forming a unity government.
</P>
<P>
Barak blasted Netanyahu for playing tricks to split the Labor
Party and confuse the general public with the talk of the unity
government.
</P>
<P>
He urged Netanyahu "to admit he is an utter failure in
everything." "National unity is a facade, a sure recipe for a
government of shame," he said.
</P>
<P>
Barak's chief opponent Yossi Beilin also opposed national
unity, saying that "instead of national unity, we will get
national paralysis."
</P>
<P>
Labor's secretary-general Nissim Zvili expressed cautious
support to the unity government, saying it should be based on
the goal of the country during a time of crisis. But he added
that the tendency within the party was preferring remaining in
the opposition to joining the unity government.
</P>
<P>
Israel Radio quoted senior Labor sources as saying that Peres
would likely win strong backing if Netanyahu agreed to evenly
divide the Cabinet seats in the future unity government.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, both Peres' and Netanyahu's aides hinted that
Peres might join the Netanyahu government on his own if he
failed to convince his party to support him. This will also give
legitimacy to the government because of Peres' influence abroad
as the leading architect of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Inside the Likud, tension is mounting because of Netanyahu's
renewed talk of the unity government.
</P>
<P>
Likud's ruling partner Tsomet announced its opposition to
national unity, while another coalition partner the National
Religious Party came out unequivocally against such
option. Netanyahu cannot succeed in forming a unity government
without substantial support within his own coalition.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on reports of forming a national unity government
in Israel, the PNA expressed welcome to the idea, saying it
could contribute to advancing the stalled peace process.
</P>
<P>
"At least it means there would be people in the government who
know Oslo, who worked for the peace agreement from the
beginning," said Abu Rudeineh, PNA secretary-general. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Deputies Address Inquiry to Provincial Government (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 13 (Xinhua) -- An inquiry sent recently to the
Provincial People's Congress of northeast China's Liaoning
Province by ten of its deputies has drawn the attention of top
provincial leaders.
</P>
<P>
With more than 2,000 years of feudal rule in China, ordinary
Chinese in the past feared officials and dared not state their
complaints directly.
</P>
<P>
But according to Quan Shuren, chairman of the Liaoning
Provincial People's Congress of, "the situation is rapidly
changing with the nation's efforts to advocate a greater sense of
democracy and encourage more political participation."
</P>
<P>
During the recently-closed fifth session of the Eighth People's
Congress of Liaoning, Jin Xisheng and nine other deputies
submitted a joint inquiry to the conference, expressing their
dissatisfaction with the government's response to one of their
proposals and asking for explanation and clarification.
</P>
<P>
Under a related Chinese law, NPC deputies who are not satisfied
with the written response to a proposal may submit inquiries,
which must be answered face-to-face and within a designated
period.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Deputies Address Inquiry to Provincial Government (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At the beginning of last year, Jin, director of the No.1
Lawyer's Firm of Shenyang and another nine deputies submitted a
proposal advising of the need to channel more water from the
nearby Dahuofang Reservoir. Doing so would settle the pollution
problems in the two rivers running through Shenyang, the capital
city of Liaoning, they maintained.
</P>
<P>
Nearly half a year later, they received a response from the
provincial government that their proposal has been rejected.
</P>
<P>
Jin said, "We are not satisfied with the simple response."
</P>
<P>
Owing to the lack of water for diluting pollutants, the
environmental quality of the rivers had steadily worsened and
caused great harm to the residents living in the area, Jin
said. "As deputies, it is our responsibility and obligation to
urge the relevant departments to take immediate action," he said.
</P>
<P>
Dahuofang Reservoir, the biggest in the province located some
100 km away from Shenyang, has a water storage capacity of 2.1
billion cubic meters. Although a diversion project had been built
and some 14 million cubic meters of water is channeled to Shenyang
yearly, this amount was believed to be far from enough.
</P>
<P>
According to Jin, the lack of water for environmental
improvement was the leading contributory factor to deterioration
of the water quality in the rivers running through Shenyang.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Deputies Address Inquiry to Provincial Government (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"This problem had caused wide concern from the residents," he
said. "The related departments that hold the power to allocate
water resources in Dahuofang Reservoir should fully consider the
residents' concerns."
</P>
<P>
He also said reconstruction was needed for a dam which was
expected to help channel water from the Dahuofang Reservoir to
Shenyang and had been destroyed by a flood several years ago,
leading to serious pollution of the daily freshwater supply in
more than 160 wells.
</P>
<P>
The deputies' inquiry was passed on to the the provincial
government. Several top provincial officials, including those in
charge of water resource management, soon met with Jin and his
fellow deputies.
</P>
<P>
The officials said that three measures would be taken to settle
the water shortage problem: an extension project to increase the
discharge of river canals in the urban area; a 30 million yuan
(3.7 million US dollars) construction project to rebuild the
destroyed dam; and a decision to allow additional six million
cubic meters of water to be channeled from the Dahuofang Reservoir
to Shenyang for environmental improvement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Congress Deputies Address Inquiry to Provincial Government (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The deputies were satisfied with the response, and were told
that all construction work should be completed by the end of this
year and the water in the rivers should be clean and limpid by May.
</P>
<P>
"The law and the people gave us deputies the supervisory power,
and I am very glad that I fully used the power," Jin said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese constitution stipulates that if more than ten
people are dissatisfied with a government response to a problem,
they may ask that the related authorities to dismiss certain
officials from office.
</P>
<P>
"The action of the ten deputies has not only promoted the
government's work but also helped to enhance the communication
between the government and the commoners, and I am very grateful
for that," said Vice-Governor Xu Wencai.
</P>
<P>
He said that through this event he saw both the growing sense
of democracy among the common people and the increased role of the
public in the political process.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, statistics show, a total of 243 proposals had been
submitted by deputies to the fifth session of the Eighth
Provincial People's Congress earlier this year -- the most ever
reported from the provincial people congresses.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
