<HEADLINE> Tea Party To Mark Mwalimu Nyerere's 75th Birthday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Trustees of Mwalimu Nyerere
Foundation will this evening hold a tea party to mark former
President Julius Nyerere's 75th birthday.
</P>
<P>
The foundation's Executive Director, Joseph Butiku was quoted
by Daily News today, as saying that the party to be held here,
will be attended by about 1,000 people including Nyerere and
President Benjamin Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
The director named other dignitaries to attend the party as OAU
Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salim, Zanzibar President Salmin
Amour, retired President Ali Hassan Mwinyi and retired Zanzibar
presidents Aboud Jumbe and Idris Abdul Wakil.
</P>
<P>
According to Butiku, the party will also be attended by heads of
diplomatic missions in Tanzania and special envoys, including those
representing US President Bill Clinton and French President Jacque
Chirac.
</P>
<P>
