<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 50 Percent of Deaths in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 50 percent of deaths in
Zimbabwe are diet-related, according to John Gooch, a leading
nutritionist with the Department of Biochemistry at the
University of Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
A recent study by the university showed that the increase in
chronic diseases was due to eating disorders. It was found that
an increasing number of people in the urban areas were eating
mostly refined food without the necessary nutrients such as
fibre.
</P>
<P>
John Gooch said, ''diabetes is a huge problem because people are
eating more and more refined foods and sugar.''
</P>
<P>
He added that the current local diet lacked the fibre that
traditional foods possessed and this was contributing to the current
surge in diabetes cases and also the increase in cases of heart
diseases. enditem

