<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Builds More Key Construction Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Zhejiang, a booming coastal
province in east China, plans to invest 16 billion yuan (1.93
billion US dollars) in building 59 crucial projects this year.
</P>
<P>
Of the listed projects, 15 are in the field of agriculture and
water conservancy, 15 in transport and communications and
telecommunications, 11 in electric power development, 13 in raw
materials industries, three in public welfare facilities and two
in service trade, Shen Dishen, a Zhejiang provincial government
official in charge of key project construction, announced at a
press briefing held in Hangzhou Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen projects are expected to go into partial or full
operation this year.
</P>
<P>
Local statistics show that Zhejiang built 54 major construction
projects last year, using a total investment of 12.86 billion
yuan, accounting for half of its aggregate investment in the
1990-95 period. Nineteen of the projects had become operational by
the end of last year. 
</P>
