<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tower Marking Crossing of Longitude, Latitude to be Built in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 13 (Xinhua) -- A tower marking the intersection
of 120 degrees east longitude and 30 degrees north latitude is
expected to be completed this July in Fuyang city in east China's
Zhejiang province.
</P>
<P>
There are 11 crossing points of longitude and latitude in
China. The point in Dongsheng Village, Dayuan Town in Fuyang is
the only one with favorable transportation conditions.
</P>
<P>
The 120 degrees east longitude is the standard line for Beijing
Time. Along the 30 degrees north latitude are located several
world famous wonders, including the Bermuda Triangle, a triangular
region in the Atlantic Ocean, the Himalayas, and Egyptian pyramids.
</P>
<P>
The tower will turn the abstract concepts of longitude and
latitude into visible objects, thus helping to increase the public
understanding of science, according to geology experts.
</P>
<P>
The tower will be 30 meters high. There will be a small
perpendicular passage in the center of the tower. At noon time,
the sunshine will go through the passage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
