<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seven Tourist Zones Built in Tianjin City Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 13 (Xinhua) -- This biggest coastal city in
north China has built seven tourist and scenic zones, which have
attracted tens of millions of tourists each year.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has increased efforts in improvement of tourism
infrastructure over the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
The seven special tourism zones consist of the downtown zone
with the Haihe River as the axis, the beach holiday zone, the
Jixian County famous historical site zone, the Xiqing folk custom
one, the Wuqing holiday resort zone with a shooting ground and a
forest park, the Jinghai rural scenery zone, and the Lake Dongli
holiday zone in which a golf course has been built.
</P>
<P>
With rapid growth in both the number of tourists and tourism
income, Tianjin has become one of the ten leading tourist cities
in China.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Tianjin received 24.76 million domestic and overseas
tourists, earning an income of 21.12 billion yuan. Some 233,000
tourists from overseas visited the city last year, creating 152
million US dollars in foreign exchange. 
</P>
