incidents that have occurred in several parts of the country in
the run-up to the general elections, adding that not all of the
incidents were masterminded by a certain group of persons as some
of them happened spontaneously.
</P>
<P>
He said anyone involved in a disturbance deserved stern
measures, and ABRI was ready to safeguard the general elections.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia's three political parties -- PPP, Golkar and the
Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) -- are busy preparing for the
May 29 election.
</P>
