<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Ports of Entry to Increase Cooperation with Those in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 13 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen ports of entry intend to
increase cooperation with those Hong Kong after it retuns to the
embrace of the motherland on July 1, today's China Daily reports.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation will include information shared through
computer networks, administration of entry and exit of cargo and
passengers, and improving port facilities, it says.
</P>
<P>
The Investigation and Study Group on Shenzhen and Hong Kong
Port Cooperation recommended the strategies in a cooperation
proposal.
</P>
<P>
The plan will be implemented in three stages over eight years
if it is approved by both sides, says the paper.
</P>
<P>
It adds the plan will be implemented strictly on the principles
of "one country, two systems", safeguarding the nation's
interests, efficient administration and convenient entry and exit
and development for ports on both sides.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation is designed to improve port facilities,
simplify inspection procedures and create efficient ports of entry
for both sides to facilitate the increasing cargo and passenger
flow expected after July 1, the plan indicates.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted investigation group officials as saying that
port cooperation will be vital to maintaining Hong Kong's
prosperity and spurring Shenzhen's second economic take-off.
</P>
<P>
Easy and smooth flow of passengers and cargo through ports of
entry on both sides will help preserve Hong Kong's stability and
prosperity, they observed.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation began in 1982 when officials signed an agreement to
open more passage-ways between Shenzhen and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Since 1984, a working group on plant and animal inspection
organized by both sides has operated widely in the quarantine
fields.  
</P>
</TEXT>
