<DOCNO> XIE19970413.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Tergat Scores Straight Win in Half-Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 12 (Xinhua) -- World cross-country champion Paul
Tergat led his Kenyan compatriots to make a clean sweep at the
Stramilano half-marathon Saturday in Milan.
</P>
<P>
Tergat equalled a record of four consecutive wins in the event
set by countryman Moses Tanui by finishing the 21.097-kilometer
course in 1 hour and 23 seconds despite strong wind.
</P>
<P>
His winning mark was merely half a minute away from the world
mark of 59:47 set by Tanui in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Tergat, 27, took command in the five kilometers from the finish
and beat teammate Kenneth Cheriyuot by 22 seconds with another
Kenyan Jonah Koech taking home the bronze medal from the downtown
streets of Milan.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian Ronaldo Da Costa finished fourth, nearly three
minutes behind the winner.
</P>
<P>
Australian Darren Wilson, who ran the fastest half marathon
this year in Tokyo, was a distant 12th. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
